About
=====

hack: an inelegant but effective solution to a computing problem
tool: any item that can be used to achieve a goal

Tools and Hacks
===============

apachemirrorer: mirrors a dir served by apache webserver
ardulcd: an arduino powered and python driven LCD
attackprofiler: profiles attack on a server, using geoip etc
baagichhaap: detects a face in an image and draws a mustache (moochh) on it
bhuproxy: reverse proxy serves Internet via one of the bhu proxies
buzzackup: google buzz feed backup utility and static feed webpage generator
clap-player: clap to change running song in cmus
crawlerdataminer: social network data miner
image-man: multiple image processors
maatv: frontend for maa to simplifies tv episodes viewing
s3uploader: a simple python-boto based s3 uploader script
spojpdfgetter: grabs all puzzle/problem pdfs from spoj for offline fun
tcpdumpstats: creates nice stat page using tcpdump data
telnethack: HTTP over Telnet, hacks over one of the bhu switches
vpnmon: draws nice current stats of a running openvpn server

